var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Introduction","text":"<p>Smash Soda is an unofficial open source application for hosting rooms on Parsec, developed by the Soda Arcade team. It is not affiliated with Parsec.</p> <p>Smash Soda gives greater control over your Parsec session, allowing you to chat with your guests, manage gamepads and more. You can also advertise your room publically with Soda Arcade.</p> <p>Smash Soda uses a now retired SDK that Parsec used to provide to developers. Due to the SDK's terms, Smash Soda can no longer be distributed as a binary, and must be built from source. </p> <p>Be wary downloading Smash Soda builds, as it's open source nature makes it easy for people to smuggle malicious code. You should always build it from source from the official repository ( https://github.com/soda-arcade/smash-soda ) or using the installer script (https://github.com/soda-arcade/smash-soda/releases/latest/installer.bat).</p> <p>If you like Smash Soda and Soda Arcade, consider donating to help fund development!</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"getting-started/install.html","title":"Installation","text":"<p>Smash Soda must be built from source due to licensing issues. </p>"},{"location":"getting-started/install.html#installer","title":"Installer","text":"<p>The easiest way to do this is with the installer batch script at:</p> <p>https://github.com/soda-arcade/smash-soda/releases/latest/installer.bat</p> <p>Download this, then right click it and select \"Run as administrator\". The script will take you through a guided setup.</p>"},{"location":"getting-started/migration.html","title":"Migration","text":"<p>Several things have been changed from the old version of Smash Soda (Legacy) to the new version. This page outlines the changes.</p>"},{"location":"getting-started/migration.html#changes","title":"Changes","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Smash Soda's configuration files have been moved from \"C:\\Users{USERNAME}\\AppData\\Roaming\\SmashSodaTwo\" to \"C:\\Users{USERNAME}\\AppData\\Roaming\\Trybuchet\\Smash Soda\".</p> </li> <li> <p>The Smash Soda overlay application has been renamed to \"Smash Glass\", and no longer needs to be added manually. Smash Soda will automatically download it.</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"getting-started/overview.html","title":"Overview","text":"<p>The Smash Soda interface is broken up in to widgets, which can be toggled and moved around. A widget can be moved by left click and dragging it by it's title bar. A widget can be resized by left click and dragging one of it's corners.</p> <p>Analytical information about Smash Soda can be found in the bottom left corner.</p> <p>Parsec and Soda Arcade account information can be found in the bottom right corner.</p> <p>The vertical nav bar in the top left corner allows you to toggle the visibilty of widgets (hover over an icon to see which widget it corresponds to).</p>"}]}